Rating: 3
This is a terrific recipe, which I've made as is, as well as with milk chocolate bits, walnuts, and dried apricots. One tip that may be helpful: You can revitalize really dried out apricots by soaking them in boiling water for 20-30 minutes (pour enough boiling water over them to cover and let sit). Then strain and pat dry the apricots -- they are reconstituted enough for the recipe.

Rating: 2
I made these cookies for a cookie exchange. The day that I baked them, they were dry and hard. After they cooled, I packed them in cookie tins. The tins helped them become more moist and they stayed fresh for almost a week. The mix of textures worked well. I will try again next year and add walnuts.

