I haven't made cookies in years, but lost a super bowl homemade cookie pool at work. The winner had an overflowing box of mostly chocolate chip & oatmeal cookies. I knew that would happen so made these. The cook from Milwaukee convinced me with the Trader Joe comment. I made them with all dark brown unpacked sugar & toasted sliced almonds as substitutes. This is my kind of cookie. Not too sweet and loaded with different textures & flavors. I will be making these again and won't wait so long.

Rating: 3
Ok, I did make some changes, let me admit that straight away- I omitted the apricots, used toasted, slivered almonds, and added a dash of vanilla and another dash, of amaretto. I also melted the chocolate before adding it. I don't know if it was because of my alterations (although I doubt it, as others have reported the same consistency), but my cookies were extremely hard and dry- biscotti-like, in fact. However, they were quite tasty if mentally approached as biscotti, and I will make them again, in that guise.

